# Extension Smoke Test Runbook

## Purpose
Provide a consistent manual verification path for Frikfrak UI work.

## Baseline Checks
1. Run `$CompileCommand`.
2. Launch the Extension Development Host.
3. Open `Test Frikfrak` and confirm the world scene renders.
4. Open `Test Frikfrak Teletext` and confirm:
- header time renders
- arrow navigation works
- metrics page renders
- feed pages render or fall back cleanly
- ticker remains alive

## If Hooks Are In Scope
- verify the local core server is running
- verify hook events appear in the `Frikfrak Hooks` output channel
- verify visible telemetry updates in the UI

## If Docs Only Changed
- skip runtime unless the docs changed the declared operating model for implementation work
- still ensure plan and agent-self files agree
